(fifthQuint)ACTH Gel Therapy in Rheumatoid Arthritis.

 This study is for people who are currently taking a biologic therapy for Rheumatoid Arthritis and who are still experiencing symptoms.

 Subjects are given the ACTH gel to take twice each week for 12 weeks as a supplement to current therapies.

 Subjects are required to visit the clinic for a baseline visit, at 2 weeks, 4 weeks, 8 weeks and 12 weeks.

 We will obtain a blood sample for research purposes.

